PN,36902
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1784465300
OL,3,CBurnham will be first PM for 50 years
OL,4,Cwith seat in north-west England
OL,6,FHe will be the first prime minister
OL,7,Fwith a seat in the North West since
OL,8,FLabour's Harold Wilson, who was MP for
OL,9,FHuyton in Merseyside throughout his
OL,10,Ftwo stints in Downing Street from 1964-
OL,11,F70 and 1974-76.
OL,13,FIn the five decades between Mr Wilson
OL,14,Fleaving office in 1976 and the start
OL,15,Fof Mr Burnham's premiership in 2026,
OL,16,F11 people held the job of prime
OL,17,Fminister.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36903
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1784465300
OL,3,CBurnham will be first PM for 50 years
OL,4,Cwith seat in north-west England
OL,6,FThree of them had constituencies in
OL,7,FLondon: Margaret Thatcher (Finchley),
OL,8,FBoris Johnson (Uxbridge & South
OL,9,FRuislip) and most recently Sir Keir
OL,10,FStarmer (Holborn & St Pancras).
OL,12,FTwo had seats in south-east England,
OL,13,FDavid Cameron (Witney in Oxfordshire)
OL,14,Fand Theresa May (Maidenhead in
OL,15,FBerkshire), and two were in eastern
OL,16,FEngland: John Major (Huntingdon in
OL,17,FCambridgeshire) and Liz Truss (South
OL,18,FWest Norfolk).
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36904
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1784465300
OL,3,CBurnham will be first PM for 50 years
OL,4,Cwith seat in north-west England
OL,6,FThe four other prime ministers between
OL,7,F1976 and 2026 had constituencies far
OL,8,Ffrom Westminster, though none were in
OL,9,Fthe North West: Jim Callaghan
OL,10,Frepresented Cardiff South East in
OL,11,FWales, Tony Blair's seat was
OL,12,FSedgefield in north-east England,
OL,13,FGordon Brown represented Kirkcaldy &
OL,14,FCowdenbeath in Scotland, and Rishi
OL,15,FSunak's seat was Richmond in Yorkshire.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36905
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1784465300
OL,3,CBurnham will be first PM for 50 years
OL,4,Cwith seat in north-west England
OL,6,FAlong with Harold Wilson and Andy
OL,7,FBurnham, only one other prime minister
OL,8,Fsince the start of the 20th century
OL,9,Fhas represented a seat in the North
OL,10,FWest: the Conservative Arthur Balfour,
OL,11,Fwho was MP for Manchester East during
OL,12,Fhis premiership from 1902-05.
OL,14,FMr Balfour's immediate predecessor as
OL,15,Fprime minister, his uncle Lord
OL,16,FSalisbury, is the most recent example
OL,17,Fin UK history of a politician who
OL,18,Fspent their entire time as premier as
OL,19,Fa member of the House of Lords, rather
OL,20,Fthan as an MP representing a
OL,21,Fconstituency.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,370,360,120,260,000,100
PN,36906
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F369A1784465300
OL,3,CBurnham will be first PM for 50 years
OL,4,Cwith seat in north-west England
OL,6,FNone of the eight prime ministers
OL,7,Fbetween 1902 and 1940 held seats in
OL,8,Fsouthern or eastern England.
OL,10,FBut starting in 1940, when Winston
OL,11,FChurchill first became prime minister,
OL,12,Fconstituencies in the south and east
OL,13,Fof the UK have been heavily
OL,14,Frepresented in Downing Street, with 11
OL,15,Fof the 19 PMs since that date holding
OL,16,Fseats in these areas of the country.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/6
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
